52557e46-5a6f-4d73-afa4-8fe9038098f6.00b44943-1b8c-4424-93da-de1583ee839c.description=
Iterates through a list of values. If the list changes while running, the updates will be appended to the list.

Inputs\:
separator - The list separator (or delimiter).
list - The list to be split

Responses\:
has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned.
failure - failed to process the list.
no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list.

Returns\:
The current element of the list, if the response is has more

52557e46-5a6f-4d73-afa4-8fe9038098f6.description=
Summary\: For each ${sanSwitchList}, determine activeConfigList, and foundActiveFidList.  Build a unique list of 1 "example" IP (for future ssh across fabric) per "zoning\: ON" activeconfig.


Getting FID / ActiveConfig Zoning Notes (for HIE)\:
 Rule \#1\: If virtualFabricsEnabled, then only 1 FID zoning\:ON\!\!
 Rule \#2\: 1 activeConfig zoning config on switch (US and UK Both).  We will use presence of active zoning config, during discovery.

Brocade Commands ran to discover FID/activeConfig\: 
proc stateful_get_activeconfig {router FID} {
  global spawn_id
  if {$FID \=\= ""} {return [string trim [lindex [grep "ON" [run_commands_quiet [list "switchshow | grep zoning"] $router 30]] 2] ")("]}
  set raw [run_commands_quiet [list "fosexec --fid all -cmd \"switchshow\" | grep \"zoning\\\|FID\" | grep \"FID\: $FID\" -B1 | grep zoning"] $router]
  set zoning_on_flag 0;
  set fidEnabled 1;
  set activeFidNum 0;
  foreach fidline [split $raw "\n"] {
    \# puts [split $fidline]
    switch -glob -- $fidline {
      "*OFF*" {puts "proc stateful_get_activeconfig\: Provided FID $FID does not have zoning ON"; exit 151515;}
      "*ON*" {
        \# puts ON\:FIDLINE\:$fidline
        return [string trim [lindex $fidline 2] ")("]
     }
      "*equires VF to be enable*" {
        return [lindex [grep "cfg\:" [run_commands_quiet [list "cfgactvshow | grep fg\:" {}] $router 30]] 1]
        \# return [string trim [lindex [grep "ON" [run_commands_quiet [list "switchshow | grep zoning"] $router 30]] 2] ")("]
      }
      default {}
    }
  }
  puts "proc stateful_get_activeconfig\: Could not determine zoning\:ON activeconfig for FID\=${FID}"; exit 25252;
}



Inputs\:
sanSwitchList
testMode

Outputs\:
IPs\: ,,
